# Code Style Guidelines

## Python Code Style
- Use snake_case for variable and function names
- Use PascalCase for class names
- Use descriptive variable names (e.g., `deleted`, `skipped`, `track_list`)
- Add comments for complex logic, especially KiCAD-specific operations
- Preserve original comments when making modifications

## Documentation Style
- Use clear, descriptive function and class names
- Add docstrings for complex functions
- Use inline comments for KiCAD API operations
- Maintain both English and Japanese documentation versions

## Makefile Style
- Use consistent indentation (tabs, not spaces)
- Group related operations together
- Use descriptive target names
- Add comments for complex shell operations
- Use `@` prefix for user-facing echo commands

## File Organization
- Keep related files together (script + icon + design files)
- Use consistent naming patterns across all files
- Maintain clear separation between source and target files
- Use relative paths where possible

## Error Messages
- All user-facing messages must be in English
- Use clear, actionable error messages
- Provide feedback for successful operations
- Use consistent formatting for status messages